# onboarding/team.md — This user's team context

> Populated by the assistant after the user answers "What team/department
> are you on?" during first-run setup. Pulled from the KB. **Edit the KB
> markdown, not this file** — the local copy refreshes on each
> `scripts/sync-kb` run.

## Source of truth

- **People in the KB:** `core/people/` (one file per person).
- **Team rows in the KB:** `core/teams/<team-slug>.md` — lean row with
  lead, members, mission. Departments mirror the new-hire flow:
  Product, Marketing, Program Advisor, Coaching, Parent Experience,
  Academics, Ops, Life Skills.
- **Long-form team pages:** `archive/teams/<team-slug>.md` — mission
  detail, current OKRs, rituals, norms.
- **User's team:** *(filled during setup — slug matching one of
  `core/teams/`)*
- **User's team file paths:** *(filled during setup — both the core row
  and the archive page)*

## What gets cached here

### The team in one sentence
*(filled automatically from `core/teams/<team-slug>.md` `mission` field
or first body line)*

### Members + their owned areas
*(filled from `core/people/` rows where `team == <user-team>`. Each
member's `owns` list / role gives the area.)*

### Current projects / OKRs
*(filled from `core/projects/` rows where `team == <user-team>` and
`status` ∈ `active`/`planned`. Goal context from `core/goals/`.)*

### Rituals + cadences
*(standup day, demo day, review cadence — filled from the
`archive/teams/<team-slug>.md` "Rituals" section)*

### Team norms
*(writing norms, review rules, on-call / pager policy — filled from the
`archive/teams/<team-slug>.md` "Norms" section)*

## Refresh cadence

- **On every session start:** after `scripts/sync-kb`, if any commit
  since last sync touched `core/people/`, `core/teams/<team-slug>.md`,
  `archive/teams/<team-slug>.md`, `core/projects/` (filtered by team),
  or `core/goals/` (filtered by team) → re-cache.
- **On role/team change the user mentions:** ask the gate question,
  swap team, re-cache. Also promote the change to the user's
  `core/people/<gh-username>.md` row.

